250 g Ground Turkey
85 g Tortilla Chips
1 cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
3 tbsp Guacamole
43 mL Creamy Dressing
2 unit(s) Green Onion
1 unit(s) Black Beans
1 unit(s) Tomato
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Drain, then rinse black beans.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then turkey and beans. Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 5-6 min.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat. Add Mexican Seasoning and cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread tortilla chips out evenly onto a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Top with turkey-bean mixture, then cheddar cheese.

Bake nachos in the middle of the oven until cheese is golden-brown and melted, 4-5 min.

Meanwhile, thinly slice green onions.
Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces.

Divide nachos between plates, then sprinkle with tomatoes and green onions.
Dollop guacamole and creamy dressing over top.

If you've opted to get turkey, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the chorizo.**